{{Quote|You follow best by following from in front. Thus your prey never knows that he's not actually the predator.|Unidentified naval crewman describing the term to [[Garik Loran]]|<ref name="X-Wing: Wraith Squadron">''[[X-Wing: Wraith Squadron]]''</ref>}}
"'''Follow best'''" was a catchphrase from Standard [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Imperial Intelligence/Legends|Intelligence]] doctrine. It was used by [[Zsinj]] when he referred to some of his traps.<ref name="X-Wing: Wraith Squadron" />

When [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Apwar Trigit]] used the term in a conversation to an undercover [[Garik Loran|Face Loran]]&mdash;who was posing as [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Zurel Darillian]]&mdash;the Imperial officer was surprised that his subordinate did not know the term. He described follow best as term that had been "practically reflex" among former Imperial Intelligence officers and should have been "second nature" to someone like Darillian.<ref name="X-Wing: Wraith Squadron" />

